column1: OMAP-14: Organ Mapping Antibody Panel (OMAP) for Multiplexed Antibody-Based Imaging of the Kidney using Cyclical Immunofluorescence (CyCIF)

column24: rationale
This marker defines proximal tubule epithelial cells (PTECs-S1/S2/S3) throughout the cortex and outer stripe of the outer medulla.
This marker defines collecting duct (CD)-principal cells throughout the kidney.

This marker defines vascular smooth muscle cells (VSMCs) in the walls of arteries and in vascular bundles in the outer medulla. In addition, it is present in peritubular and periglomerular interstitial myofibroblasts (MFs).
This marker helps define cortical collecting duct (CCD, distal convoluted tubules  (DCT) and connecting tubules (CNT). In conjunction with SLC12A3, it also helps define the cortical collecting duct.
This marker defines tubular basement membrane (TBM), glomerular (GN) capsules, and the peritubular extracellular matrix (ECM).

This marker, in conjunction with UMOD, identifies the thick ascending limb in the cortex and outer medulla. It is also present in UMOD negative cells in the cortex and outer medulla (collecting duct). Low levels of this marker are seen in AQP1 positive proximal tubular epithelial cells.
This marker defines discrete clusters of distal convoluted tubules throughout the cortex.
Used to visualize SLC12A3.
This marker defines the S1 and S2 proximal tubular epithelial cells in the cortex.
Used to visualize SLC5A12.
This marker defines podocytes and is localized to the plasma membrane compared to other podocyte markers such as PDXL and NES.
This marker defines discrete groups of thick ascending limb (TAL) tubules.
Used to visualize UMOD.

This marker defines podocytes and is localized to the cytoplasm. This is distinct from PODXL (podocyte plasma membrane), TNS1, which stains mesangial cells, and PECAM1, which stains endothelial cells in the glomerulus.
Used to visualize NES.
This marker defines glomerular mesangial cells. In addition, it is present in vascular smooth muscle cells in some (but not all) juxta-glomerular arterioles.
Used to visualize TNS1.
This marker defines podocytes, specifically the cytoplasm and plasma membrane.
This marker defines all endothelial cells.
This marker defines podocyte nuclei. It is absent from glomerular endothelial cells and mesangial cells.

This marker defines podocytes (plasma membranes only), specifically the basolateral plasma membrane, and all tubular epithelial distal to proximal tubules including descending and ascending thin limb and thick ascending limb of the loop of henle (DTL, ATL, TAL), distal convoluted tubules (DCTs), connecting tubules (CNTs), and collecting duct (CD).
This marker defines the glomerular basement membrane (GBM) and capsule, as well as some tubular basement membrane structures. It is distinct from COL4A1/2, which stains mesangial matrix.
